Frederick Hollands (7 October 1822 – 30 June 1898) was an English professional cricketer who played for Kent County Cricket Club. 
He was born in Leeds, Kent in 1822 and played for the county team between 1849 and 1859. He made 31 appearances in first-class cricket matches, mainly for Kent, and played in a number of non-first-class matches as a professional. He died at Broomfield in 1898 aged 75.
